:"
            <p>Two new versions of Ruby On Rails have been released today.  As well as including a number of bugfixes they contain fixes for some security issues.  The full details of each of the vulnerabilities are available on the <a href="http://groups.google.com/group/rubyonrails-security">rubyonrails-security mailing list</a>.  We <strong>strongly</strong> urge you to update production Rails applications as soon as possible. Rather than post the advisories individually to this blog, I’ll just link to the google talk archives.</p>


	<p>Install the latest version using <ins>gem install rails</ins>. Or if you’re using bundler, edit your gemfile and run <ins>bundle update rails</ins>.</p>


	<h2>Summaries</h2>


	<p>Affecting 2.x.x and 3.0.x</p>


	<ul>
	<li><a href="http://groups.google.com/group/rubyonrails-security/t/f02a48ede8315f81"><span class="caps">XSS</span> Risk in mail_to :encode=&gt;:javascript</a> CVE-2011-0446</li>
		<li><a href="http://groups.google.com/group/rubyonrails-security/t/2d95a3cc23e03665"><span class="caps">CSRF</span> Bypass Risk</a> CVE-2011-0447</li>
	</ul>


	<p>Affecting 3.0.x only</p>


	<ul>
	<li><a href="http://groups.google.com/group/rubyonrails-security/t/362f1fbc1761b336">Filter Problems on Case Insensitive Filesystems</a> CVE-2011-0449</li>
		<li><a href="http://groups.google.com/group/rubyonrails-security/t/b658902cf6bf4eed">Potential <span class="caps">SQL</span> Injection with limit()</a> CVE-2011-0448</li>
	</ul>
